  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "U8pWK06ImW64xdmsggUcH/g9UHs=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# masterchef accumulator pattern enables per-token revenue tracking\n\nThe POWA contracts use a well-established DeFi pattern (originating from SushiSwap's MasterChef) where a global `accRevenuePerShare` accumulator tracks total revenue accrued per unit of token supply. Each account stores a `rewardDebt` checkpoint \u2014 the accumulator value at last interaction \u2014 and `pending` unclaimed revenue.\n\nWhen revenue is deposited:\n```\naccRevenuePerShare += (revenueAmount * PRECISION) / totalSupply\n```\n\nWhen an account is updated:\n```\naccumulated = balance * accRevenuePerShare / PRECISION\nearned = accumulated - rewardDebt\npending += earned\nrewardDebt = accumulated\n```\n\nThis is an **on-chain implementation detail** that the off-chain document model should NOT replicate. The document model instead captures the business-level view: epoch config, total revenue, per-epoch allocation percentages, and claim events. The accumulator math runs on-chain; the document model stores inputs and outputs.\n\nKey insight for modeling: the document model needs \"Revenue Configuration\" (inputs) and \"Distribution Records\" (outputs) but NOT the accumulator state itself.\n\n---\n\nRelevant Notes:\n- [[powa-revenue-distribution model captures epoch-based token revenue sharing]]\n- [[powa document model bridges on-chain contracts with off-chain governance]]\n\nTopics:\n- [[schema design]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
    }
  },
